      <acqinfo id="aspace_5819b7d79c66074c5acda0252596e9de">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011, it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_7dcce7fecd086ecbca38288edbaf6c0f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_0dd9106e88a869c3dc997305cf4e53be">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_d0b9e5e598a04c45f1911f4fe828ae4e">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by F. B. Siegrist, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_7e8f73e3e8d17a94dbfa8152649350f5">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>The collection was removed from filing cabinets which housed bookplates by individual artists.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_f131730d33e216ea741c36136888451c">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Frank B. Siegrist (d. 1969) was a partner, along with his brother Ivan, in the Siegrist Engraving Company, which was founded in Kansas City, MO, in 1902 by their father, Henry Siegrist.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_45ba28af74244c7c9d06d584a834a8a3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains signed artist's proofs for bookplates designed by F. B. Siegrist.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
